Nvidia under Huang did everything we hope our greatest companies will do: t=
hey had a long-term vision, they innovated relentlessly to find new markets=
 and applications for industry-leading technology, and when a world-changin=
g opportunity presented itself with large language models, they were ready =
to take advantage of it, for a long-term benefit that may forever be unmeas=
urable. This is the behavior our government apparently wants to punish?

Now granted, the demand for Nvidia=E2=80=99s GPUs came on so suddenly and i=
n such an overwhelming amount that the company had to pick-and-choose who g=
ot allocation; that the company may have preferred companies it was investe=
d in, or who only bought from Nvidia, or who were willing to host DGX cloud=
 is hardly a crime: it=E2=80=99s the reward for building a product that peo=
ple want. It=E2=80=99s nuts to me that the DOJ is even considering this cas=
e.

Moreover, while CUDA does provide some amount of lock-in, Nvidia=E2=80=99s =
focus on building fully integrated AI systems that scale to massive trainin=
g clusters is a major factor in their dominance as well. A key part of this=
 integration was the March 2019 acquisition of Mellanox ( https://nvidianew=
s.nvidia.com/news/nvidia-completes-acquisition-of-mellanox-creating-major-f=
orce-driving-next-gen-data-centers ) ; investors were impressed, as you can=
 see from the stock chart:

Oh wait, you can=E2=80=99t see anything, because while Nvidia=E2=80=99s sto=
ck was up slightly on the news of the acquisition, it was up to only $4; it=
=E2=80=99s $108 after the DOJ=E2=80=99s announcement. In other words, Huang=
 and Nvidia made a massive bet on the future, they were right, and because =
they were right =E2=80=94 with no other meaningful change in their strategy=
 =E2=80=94 our government wants to investigate them.

The fact of the matter is is that there is feverish investment in the attem=
pt to diversify away from Nvidia, from chips to software to services. Indee=
d, most of the customers who aren=E2=80=99t getting all of the Nvidia chips=
 they want =E2=80=94 which the DOJ apparently feels they are entitled to, e=
ven if supply is still short =E2=80=94 are investing billions in developing=
 in-house alternatives. The market is very much working: Nvidia is being ju=
stly rewarded, and competition is coming. The only failure that is happenin=
g is the news of this absurd investigation.

